                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2252: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Warren</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-09-24T16:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 24, 1921—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 24—10:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>315. Your 158, September 21, 5 p.m. Foreign Office state they have had a report
                    from Vladivostok that a certain Australian is negotiating with (American Banking
                    Corporation?) [for a loan] and have telegraphed Vladivostok and Dairen for
                    further information which they will communicate to me when received. They add
                    that Japanese Government has nothing to do with the matter and that it is
                    against their policy to finance or to negotiate with Merkulov’s government as
                    distinct from Chita. Stevens informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Warren</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
